<HEADLINE> Turkey Welcomes Clinton's appointment of Albright </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, December 6 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Prime Minister
Necmettin Erbakan and Foreign Minister Tansu Ciller today
welcomed U.S. President Bill Clinton's appointment of Madeleine
Albright as new U.S. secretary of state.
</P>
<P>
Erbakan said that Albright had impressed him as a "positive
and constructive person." He expressed his hope that she would
contribute to forging better ties between Turkey and the U.S.
during Clinton's second term.
</P>
<P>
Albright met Erbakan in Ankara in July when the renewal
of the mandate of the Operation Provide Comfort (OPC) force
staying in Incirlik Air Base of Adana, southern Turkey, was
discussed between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish prime minister said he hoped Albright would pay
a visit to Ankara after her appointment is confirmed by the
U.S. Congress.
</P>
<P>
In a message of congratulation to Albright, Ciller said
that she is very pleased to celebrate Clinton's appointment of
Albright as the first woman secretary of state in the United
States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
